A DSL rule to add new conditional branches or arbitrary statement blocks is not currently supported and would require significant DSL extensions. An example of how it *might* look if such extensions existed is purely speculative:

// NOT VALID DSL - Demonstrates required feature:
// Extend getBinding() method in DefaultBindingResolver to handle Receiver nodes
@extendMethod: org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.DefaultBindingResolver.getBinding($node)

if ($node instanceof QualifiedSuperReference) {
    QualifiedSuperReference qualifiedSuperReference = (QualifiedSuperReference) $node;
    return this.getTypeBinding(qualifiedSuperReference.qualification.resolvedType);
}
else if ($node instanceof Receiver) {
    org.eclipse.jdt.internal.compiler.lookup.TypeBinding receiver = ((Receiver) $node).type.resolvedType;
    return this.getTypeBinding(receiver);
}
;;
